annotation.TEXT: Alright, it's boss time!
Hello, brick wall. Meet my AWESOME SPREAD GUN!
Apparently, a pink note block replaces the green springboard with this map skin.
Oh, that's right. After getting a mushroom, I can charge my shot.
Good thing I can dash over 1-tile gaps!
Alt. skin votes include: 1 vote for any female character, 1 vote for SNES Roll (Mega Man), 1 vote for Tetromino (Sophia III), and 1 vote for a random Bass skin.
Alright, now I'll grab it!
Demo count: 2
The game gave me RC-011 from Probotector (GB). Alright, now let's see if I can find an AWESOME SPREAD GUN in this level...
Tango, help me out here!
...Nope. He plays the same.
Alright, I've saved the Bass for last. So, let's go with a random Bass skin here...
YES YES YES!!! It's the AWESOME METAL BLADE!!!
Oh, geez. The sprite representing the cheepos this time is Castlevania's Medusa Head, which is fitting, since you probably know how nasty Medusa Heads can be in the Castlevania games...
Unfortunately, I hadn't quite reached midpoint, so I gotta start the level from the beginning.
Up next, I believe I'll go with the SNES Roll.
That last block contains just a coin. I don't need it, but my OCD wants to hit the block anyway. I'll just use shurikens from over here to hit it.
Awesome! I made it through the whole level without getting hit! Okay, now to try for six fireworks...
And now I've been launched into deep space by the green springboard! However, I will come back down in a moment...
Ah, yes. Alright then.
Oh, it felt good to tear down that wall. Now, unfortunately, my character's not very fast, so I'm probably going to miss some coins while trying to get back onto the cloud platform up ahead.
Uhh... That most definitely was not supposed to happen, and you'd better believe that I'm going to mention that on the Exploding Rabbit forums! Alright, let's try a different random Bass skin.
WHAAAAT?!?!
Quick Man, eh? Okay, now I've gotta refresh my memory as to how this skin differs from the regular Bass skin, so give me a moment here...
Yikes! ...Okay, I know I'm getting impatient, but I shouldn't be taking risks like that!
Nope. Don't need the "F". (I might've considered it if this level had lots of Buzzies and Bullet Bills...)
Oh, geez! Time limit! Okay, gotta hustle! I'll just quickly use Tango for any remotely tricky jump.
Alright, I think this is the star block, so...
I'll need to reveal a couple of hidden coin blocks to get past this part. And, it looks like Tango's required as well.
There we go. That Blooper tried to make my life difficult, but he got skewered.

Wow, that would've sucked if I didn't quite make it across that pit there! (I was hoping to land on the ledge with the hidden 1-up, but at least I could still reveal the 1-up from below by just shooting at it.)
I hope I can reach it...
Yeah, that kind of stinks, but oh, well.
I'm doing well at dodging the Medusa Heads so far...
Yeah, I'm not taking chances right now.
I felt like I barely made that jump.
Demo count: 4
I'll just let these Goombas take a lava bath...
Okay, I didn't fall into that hole this time.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results, with everybody except for Random getting at least one vote, oddly enough.
I believe that there is one place in this level where I can potentially get a 1-up combo from kicking a koopa shell, and it's just after the block that contains the star.
Oh, man! Is that what I think it is? Please tell me that's what I think it is!
I think I'll start off with Chris Akridge's vote for the duo band of "Bill Rizer and the AWESOME SPREAD GUN"! But, I'll pick a random skin for him.
Yeah, I just wanted to make sure I landed safely there. Now, there's a vine and a couple of hidden coin blocks here...
Gah! ...This isn't the original SMB where I can pass through the back tip of a Bowser flame unharmed...
...Maybe I should've called Tango for that jump...
Now, let's tear the place up with the power of the AWESOME SPREAD GUN! Oh, and be careful of the pit there.
...Huh... There is no "SNES Roll", apparently...
Oh, and just so you guys know, the characters that I haven't used in The Lost Levels yet are Samus, Simon, and Sophia III.
...Well. That just happened.
Ooh, a happy star! I guess I could use it to kill one piranha plant, but it's not gonna last long, because I'm going to enter this bonus room down here.
Let's try that again, shall we?
Okay, there's a power up in one of these blocks that I really want...
Well, I got the six fireworks, but my flagpole score sucked...
Whoops. I hit the weapon change button by accident there.
Huh. You can kill piranha plants with kicked shells in SMB Crossover. (You can't in the original SMB or Lost Levels.)
Oh, heck yeah! First power up block in this level produced an "S"! Now I just have to collect it!
Bwah... Grabbing the side of that falling platform wasn't what I intended to do...
This part seems more dangerous than usual. I guess it's because I'm not using a plumber now.
Okay, can I get the fireworks timing correct this time?
Uh, oh. Isn't this a flying cheepo level? Oh, man. I predict a lot of pain in Kaede's future...
Up next shall be Kaede from Shadow of the Ninja.
That multi-coin block was emptied out quickly!

Wait, why is that poison mushroom still here? ...Oh, right. That's how SMB Crossover works. Things don't actually despawn from simply being off screen, even if I go into a side area. Well, it's easy enough to dodge.
Demo count: 3
Eat Metal Blade, koopas!
Sliding kick! (What is this, Mega Man Soccer?)
Huzzah! Got the 6!
Nuts to these guys. I'm too impatient to gun them down now.
Alright, up next is the totally epic level known as 3-1! So, place your votes for who you want me to use next time!
I'll just let the star follow me for a bit here...
Okay, let's do this part correctly this time!
Alright, mister trolling koopa, I'm just gonna utterly destroy you down here this time, since trying to kick you for a 1-up combo is clearly out of the question.
I'm not gonna bother with the bots there.
There's another jump where I absolutely need Tango.
Hey, stop hopping over most of my bullets!
Alright, now let's not lose it to something stupid. Roll's already suffered two deaths today.
Ooh, this SML Sub/Plane music sounds good in a bonus area!
Alright, now here's the setup where there's a hidden power up that I was thinking of while I was in 1-4 last time.
Well, I'm going to assume that you meant the Mega Man 8 Roll here.
Got him! Okay, now there's a multi-coin block here, which I can empty quickly with this character. And, I'll destroy the rest of the bricks just for the heck of it.
Thank you, Tango!
I got Gemini Man this time. Does he play any different than the standard Bass?
Alright, that multi-coin block is cleaned out. Now, let's enter this bonus room over here.
I may as well reveal the poison mushroom over here before climbing the vine, so that I don't have to deal with it later.
I guess I can kick this guy for a small combo, but I'm certainly not gonna get a 1-up out of it.
Now, at the beginning of 2-4, I can potentially get a 1-up combo by kicking the first koopa shell to the right and then chasing it...
Yeah! There we go! Now to go back for the star.
Hmm... I don't trust my ability to make this jump this time, so I think I'll call in a little assistance.
Take THREE!
There's another power up hidden above this mushroom platform here, but I doubt I'll care about it...
AWESOME SPREAD GUN ACQUIRED.
Alright, I'm outta here.
So, maybe the duo band's name will be "RC-011 and the AWESOME SPREAD GUN" now? ...I don't know... It doesn't quite sound as epic...
At least I'm getting a decent amount of NP (Ninja Power... or maybe Nintendo Power. It's a shame that magazine series came to an end a couple years ago...).
Need Tango to reach these coins.
Hey there, Met. How's it going? You a NY Mets fan, by any chance?
To be continued... Yo!
Excellent!
